P/HARCOURT  – The Managing Director and Chief Executive Officer of Ochitech global services limited, Geobliss Osinachi George has charged corporate organisations in Emohua Local Government Area of Rivers State to leave up to their social corporate responsibility to ensure even development of communities under their cover. George made the remark during the closing ceremony of EMOLGA peace & unity cup Competition at Ojims collage, Rumuji organised by national Youth council of Nigeria, saying that investment in sporting activity will directly affect Youth development there by changing their narative towards positive venture. Mr. George who was the donor of the competition maintained that since peace has finally returned to the local government, that there’s urgent need to engage the Youths of the area, hence his decision to bank role the game as a way of sending signals to investors into the local government. EXPOSED - HOW LAGOS DOCTOR DISCOVERED MAJOR REASONS WHY MOST WIVES NOW HEAVILY CHEATS ON THEIR HUSBANDS AND THE PERMANENT SECRET TO SEXUALLY SATISFYING THEIR WIVES. DON'T BE A VICTIM! While thanking all the groups that Honoured him as a way of encouragement, he commended the the EMOLGA chapter of national Youth council of Nigeria for their efforts. Also speaking, the Paramount ruler Rumuji Community, Eze Christian Elechi thanked the organisers of the game for the choice of his kingdom for the competition which has put to the world that peace has return in the local government and call for more program that put the youth together. Rivers Community Barricades Afam Power Plant Rivers Govt Urges Investors To Take Advantage Of Friendly Tax Regime In Rivers On his part, the coordinator of EMOLGA chapter of national Youth council of Nigeria, Innovation Woke expressed satisfaction on the successful hosting of the game and thanked the donor for bank rolling the event even as he commended participants on their peaceful rule during the football game. High point of the game w